                     <persName id="t18250915-306-victim1547" type="victimName">Mayor, Commonality and Citizens of London<interp inst="t18250915-306-victim1547" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-306-off1654 t18250915-306-victim1547"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , and fixed to a certain dwelling-house there situated
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>EIGHT OTHER COUNTS varying the manner of laying the charge.</p>
               <p>MESSRS. BOLLAND and BERNARD conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-306-person1548">
                  JOHN 
                  THOMAS KIRKUP
               <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1548" type="surname" value="THOMAS KIRKUP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1548" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1548" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in possession of two houses, No. 4 and 5, George-alley, Fleet-market. On the night of the 7th of July, I was in No. 4 - I had information, and came home about eight o'clock at night, and between eight and nine, I saw the prisoner look over the wall leading out of Rose and Crown-court into George-alley - he was on the top of the privy - I had seen him before. I got my stick, mounted the wall, and found him crouching down with his hands on this lead. I secured him, and another person took the lead; we gave him to Johnson, and next day, by order of Mr. Montague, I compared the lead with the top of Mr. Eastwood's house in <placeName id="t18250915-306-crimeloc1657">Shoe-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-306-crimeloc1657" type="placeName" value="Shoe-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-306-crimeloc1657" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-306-off1654 t18250915-306-crimeloc1657"></join> - it corresponded exactly, nail holes and all; the house had been taken possession of by the Corporation - it was taken from the back gutter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-306-person1549">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1549" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1549" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1549" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and took charge of the prisoner, the lead weighs twenty lbs. - I matched it with a short gutter on the roof of No. 27, Shoe-lane - it corresponded.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-306-person1550">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MONTAGUE
               <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1550" type="surname" value="MONTAGUE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1550" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-person1550" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , ESQ. I am the City surveyor. This house was taken by the Corporation; Mr. Eastwood occupied it, and Mr. Watson, was the freeholder - the prisoner was not employed there.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182509150115"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. I was working next door, and got over there, for a necessary purpose - I did not move the lead.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-306-verdict1658" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-306-verdict1658" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>
